      <abstract>
        <p>On the Street photos of stylish Hamptonites at polo match</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A 21st-century Gatsby scene: the first of this summer's six Saturday Mercedes-Benz Polo Challenge matches evoked polo's 1920's and 30's golden age on Long Island. Sleek ponies, grand cars, pedigree dogs and elegant women and men promenaded within the white picket fences at Two Trees Farm in Bridgehampton. An auction aided the Leary Firefighters Foundation. Admission, $20 a carful, goes to the South Fork Breast Health Coalition.</p>
      </block>
